    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-09-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="97"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                <head>97. <gloss target="#t_Backchannel_1">Backchannel</gloss> Message From the
                    Ambassador to Chile (<persName corresp="#p_KEM_1">Korry</persName>) to the Under
                    Secretary of State for Political Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_JUA_1"
                        >Johnson</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d97fn1">Source:
                        National Security Council, Nixon Intelligence Files, Subject Files, Chile,
                        1970. Secret; Sensitive.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Santiago</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1970-09-16">September 16, 1970</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. In a separate State message I am reporting (a) the mounting pressures on the
                    Cardinal of Santiago to recognize <persName corresp="#p_AGS_1"
                        >Allende</persName>, (b) on the pressures abuilding against holdout <hi
                        rend="italic">El Mercurio</hi> and (c) the French negotiations with
                        <persName corresp="#p_AGS_1">Allende</persName>.<note n="2" xml:id="d97fn2">
                        <ref target="#d99">Document 99</ref>.</note> I would welcome very prompt
                    assistance from Washington on all three:</p>
                <p>A. [<hi rend="italic">2 lines not declassified</hi>]</p>
                <p>B. Is there some way to get First National City Bank to take heat off <hi
                        rend="italic">El Mercurio</hi>? Bank, which is preparing to fold its local
                    tent, is dunning the paper for its loans. This kind of pressure is no less
                    pernicious than that of the Communists.</p>
                <p>C. Can Department take any diplomatic action in Europe to prevent
                    rug-pulling.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
